<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-03T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-03T08:00:00-05:00" n="375" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d375">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/27729:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Standley</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kuibyshev</hi> (<hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>)</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-03T16:00:00+03:00">February 3, 1943—4
                                        p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received February 4—11:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>103. A neutral colleague has informed me that a member of the
                                Bulgarian Legation here recently told him that while the strong
                                Russo-phile sentiment in Bulgaria would not permit the sending of
                                Bulgarian troops to aid the Germans on the Russian front, the
                                Bulgarian Army would as a matter of course fight side by side with
                                the Axis forces in the event of the opening of a second front
                                anywhere else on the Continent.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Standley</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>